      "content": "okay but those stats only show the \"pro\" side though. doesn't the other side have valid points about the economic cost? like if a government takes over the whole system, doesn't that usually lead to massive debt, long wait times, and less innovation in medicine? it seems like you're basically saying the \"right\" argument is the one with the better stats, but isn't the economic risk a real fact too?",
